subSubSection.paragraph:
Palpus (
Fig. 1A, B
): patellar apophysis absent; LTA corniculate; RTA broad and flat; cimbial furrow short and indistinctive; median apophysis claw-shaped and slightly bifurcate; conductor robust and somewhat twisted; embolus thick and short.

Epigynum and endogynum (
Fig. 1C, D
): central portion of epigynal plate funnel-shaped and protuberate; copulatory opening with black circumference, situated posterior to epigynum; epigynal teeth absent; spermathecae roundish, situated close to each other.
